For detailed instructions, press the 'F1' (or '?') key at any time.

The Foundation Set includes the basic software you need to install, run and
use the UNIX Operating System on your computer. You have selected to install
this software using diskettes.

To proceed with the installation, you must place the floppy labeled
"Foundation Set: Installation" into your diskette drive and then type
'1' followed by 'ENTER' to begin installation.  The computer will display
a message on the screen when it is time for you to remove this floppy and
insert the next one.  

If you did not want to install from diskette, type '2' followed by 'ENTER'
to go back to the previous screen, to choose an installation media.
